%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Catastrophic'%20Private%20Costs%2C%20Poverty%2C%20Malnutrition%3A%20What%20Keeps%20India%20From%20Achieving%20its%20TB%20Goals%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F08%2F02171246%2FMycobacterium_tuberculosis_Bacteria_the_Cause_of_TB_5149398656.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETuberculosis%20or%20TB%2C%20one%20of%20the%20top%20infectious%20diseases%20responsible%20for%20mortality%20worldwide%2C%20is%20one%20of%20those%20diseases%20that%20majorly%20affects%20those%20in%20the%20lower%20socio-economic%20group.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%202023%20UN%20General%20Assembly%20High-Level%20Meeting%20on%20TB%20reinforced%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E2018%20commitments%20and%20targets%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20setting%20out%20new%20targets%20for%20the%20period%20of%202023-2027.%20The%20new%20targets%20include%20reaching%2090%25%20of%20people%20in%20need%20with%20TB%20prevention%20and%20care%20services%20and%20using%20a%20WHO-recommended%20rapid%20test%20as%20the%20first%20method%20of%20diagnosing%20TB.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20meeting%20also%20highlighted%20the%20provision%20of%20health%20and%20social%20benefit%20packages%20for%20all%20people%20with%20TB%20and%20the%20securing%20of%20at%20least%20one%20new%20TB%20vaccine%20that%20is%20safe%20and%20effective.%20The%20meeting%20also%20recommended%20closing%20funding%20gaps%20for%20TB%20programme%20implementation%20and%20research%20by%202027.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20we%20talk%20about%20funding%20at%20a%20macro%20level%2C%20TB%20continues%20to%20inflict%20financial%20hardships%20on%20millions%20of%20Indians%20every%20year.%20India%20has%20the%20highest%20TB%20burden%20across%20the%20world%20contributing%20to%20about%2027%25%20of%20all%20the%20TB%20cases%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Firis.who.int%2Fbitstream%2Fhandle%2F10665%2F373828%2F9789240083851-eng.pdf%3Fsequence%3D1%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWHO%E2%80%99s%20Global%20TB%20report%202023%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20India%E2%80%99s%20National%20Tuberculosis%20Elimination%20Programme%20(NTEP)%20covers%20diagnostic%20and%20therapeutic%20costs%20of%20TB%20treatment%2C%20many%20seek%20TB%20care%20privately%20for%20a%20vast%20variety%20of%20reasons%20with%20the%20most%20prominent%20among%20them%20being%20stigma.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPeople%20living%20with%20TB%20experience%20financial%20distress%20due%20to%20both%20direct%20and%20indirect%20costs.%20Taking%20loans%2C%20borrowing%20money%2C%20selling%C2%A0%20land%2C%20gold%20jewellery%20or%20any%20other%20assets%20are%20some%20measures%20people%20take%20to%20cover%20the%20cost%20of%20care.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20picture%20I%20paint%20is%20not%20a%20one-off%20scenario.%20%E2%80%98Catastrophic%E2%80%99%20spendings%20necessitated%20by%20TB%2C%20as%20highlighted%20by%20WHO%2C%20are%20direct%20and%20indirect%20costs%20of%20TB%20diagnosis%20and%20care%20which%20amount%20to%20over%2020%25%20of%20the%20TB%20patient%E2%80%99s%20household%E2%80%99s%20annual%20income.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOf%20the%2030%20high%20TB%20burden%20countries%2C%20estimates%20of%20the%20percentage%20of%20the%20population%20facing%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ecatastrophic%20health%20expenditures%20are%20particularly%20high%20for%20India%20along%20with%20Angola%2C%20Bangladesh%2C%20China%2C%20Nigeria%2C%20Sierra%20Leone%20and%20Uganda%2C%20the%20global%20report%20says.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20direct%20cost%20includes%20medical%20costs%20(involving%20registration%2C%20consultation%2C%20hospitalisation%2C%20investigation%2C%20or%20medication)%20and%20non-medical%20costs%20(food%2C%20travel%2C%20and%20nutritional%20supplements).%20Indirect%20costs%20comprise%20an%20overall%20loss%20of%20wages%20due%20to%20productivity%20loss%2C%20missed%20work%2C%20loss%20of%20time%2C%20loss%20of%20income%2C%20and%20caregiving%20work.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20more%20alarming%20as%20direct%20costs%20of%20care%20from%20private%20physicians%20are%20manifold%20compared%20to%20that%20incurred%20by%20individuals%20who%20are%20treated%20by%20NTEP%20(National%20TB%20Elimination%20Programme)%20providers%20under%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20set-up.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20high%20costs%20associated%20with%20TB%20entrap%20the%20affected%20population%C2%A0into%20a%20vicious%20cycle%20of%20poverty%20and%20disease%20which%20is%20far%20from%20WHO%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98End%20TB%E2%80%99%20goal%2C%20including%20the%20target%20that%20no%20TB%20patients%20and%20their%20households%20should%20face%20catastrophic%20costs%20due%20to%20the%20disease%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20the%20WHO%20Global%20TB%20Report%202023%2C%20about%20half%20of%20the%20TB%20patients%20and%20their%20households%20suffer%20catastrophic%20(%3E20%25%20of%20annual%20household%20income)%20total%20costs.%20A%20report%20from%20WHO%20and%20Treatment%20Action%20Group%20(TAG)%20shows%20us%20that%20there%20was%20a%20decline%20in%20global%20funding%20for%20essential%20TB%20services%2C%20from%20US%20%24%206.5%20billion%20in%202019%20to%20US%20%24%205.8%20billion%20in%202022%20which%20is%20less%20than%20half%20of%20the%20global%20target%20of%20US%20%24%2013%20billion.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECurrent%20health%20expenditure%20(%25%20of%20GDP)%20in%20South%20Asia%20in%202020%20was%20less%20than%204.18%20and%20significantly%20lower%20in%20countries%20like%20India%2C%20according%20to%20World%20Bank%20data.%20According%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98s%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fbudget-interim-health-nutrition-declines%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enews%20report%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20in%20the%20interim%20Indian%20budget%20presented%20for%20the%20year%202024-25%2C%20the%20budget%20allocation%20for%20the%20department%20of%20health%20and%20family%20welfare%2C%20the%20department%20of%20health%20research%20and%20key%20nutrition%20programmes%20have%20dipped%20for%20the%20fiscal%20year%202024-25%20as%20compared%20to%202023-24%20budget%20estimates%2C%20when%20adjusted%20for%20inflation.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EContrary%20to%20the%20allocation%20of%20Rs%2086%2C175%20crores%20(as%20per%20budget%20estimates)%20for%20the%20department%20of%20health%20and%20family%20welfare%20in%20FY%202023-24%2C%20the%20allocation%20for%202024-25%20increased%20to%20Rs%2087%2C656%20crores.%20However%2C%20when%20considering%20inflation%20at%20a%20rate%20of%205%25%2C%20this%20apparent%20increase%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eactually%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20amounts%20to%20a%20decrease%20of%203.17%25%20in%20real%20terms%2C%20the%20news%20report%20says.%20Thus%2C%20the%20budget%20for%20the%20health%20and%20family%20welfare%20department%20has%20actually%20decreased%20when%20adjusted%20for%20inflation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20goal%20to%20achieve%20elimination%20of%20TB%C2%A0can%20be%20completed%20by%20reaching%20the%20lower%20socio-economic%20and%20remote%20sections%20of%20vulnerable%20communities.%C2%A0%20Inadequate%20funding%20and%20inaccessible%20resources%20are%20major%20hindrances%20in%20reaching%20the%20desired%20goal%20of%20ending%20TB%20worldwide.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20global%20aspirations%20to%20eliminate%20TB%20by%202030%20reflect%20crucial%20ambition%20and%20determination.%20India%20aims%20to%20eliminate%20TB%20by%202025.%20However%2C%20with%20current%20funding%20levels%20and%20opportunities%2C%20the%20aim%20to%20end%20the%20TB%20crisis%20by%202030%20appears%20challenging%20to%20achieve%20unless%20addressed%20timely%2C%20leaving%20vulnerable%20communities%20at%20risk%20of%20further%20devastation%20due%20to%20TB%20in%20the%20latter%20half%20of%20the%2021st%20century.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEncouragingly%2C%20ongoing%20scientific%20advances%20such%20as%20newer%20tools%20to%20screen%20and%20diagnose%20TB%20and%20newer%20treatment%20regimens%2C%20as%20well%20as%20new%20vaccines%20in%20the%20pipeline%20offer%20genuine%20promise%20in%20combating%20the%20epidemic%20by%202030.%20Yet%2C%20achieving%20this%20goal%20will%20demand%20a%20significant%20increase%20in%20funding%20and%20finding%20innovative%20ways%20to%20reduce%20direct%20and%20indirect%20costs%20of%20TB%20care%20to%20disrupt%20this%20vicious%20circle.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIncreasing%20awareness%20of%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20services%20for%20TB%20elimination%2C%20continued%20decentralization%20of%20services%20and%20dispelling%20negative%20attitudes%20about%20the%20national%20TB%20programme%20may%20encourage%20impoverished%20affected%20people%C2%A0to%20avail%C2%A0free%20care.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESocial%20determinants%20of%20health%2C%20such%20as%20poverty%2C%20malnutrition%2C%20and%20crowded%20living%20conditions%C2%A0are%20equally%20important%20factors%20which%20are%20overlooked%20while%20planning%20a%20comprehensive%20TB%20control%20strategy%20in%20many%20South%20Asian%20countries%2C%20including%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EFarhat%20Mantoo%20joined%20Doctors%20Without%20Borders%2FM%C3%A9decins%20Sans%20Fronti%C3%A8res%20(MSF)%20in%202003%20and%20has%20been%20working%20in%20different%20capacities%20nationally%20as%20well%20as%20internationally.%20Currently%2C%20she%20is%20the%20Executive%20Director%20of%20MSF%20South%20Asia.%20She%20has%20a%20specialisation%20in%20medical%20anthropology%2C%20communication%2C%20hospital%20management%20and%20human%20resources%20apart%20from%20being%20trained%20in%20humanitarian%20assistance%20linked%20to%20international%20humanitarian%20affairs.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709193125000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fcatastrophic-private-costs-poverty-malnutrition-what-keeps-india-from-achieving-its-tb-goals%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20against%20the%20global%20deadline%20of%20TB%20elimination%20by%202030%2C%20India%20has%20set%20the%20deadline%20for%202025.%20It%20is%20an%20ambitious%20target.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Biden%20doing%20everything%20to%20improve%20visas%20process%20%26amp%3B%20Green%20Card%20backlog%3A%20White%20House%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709192840000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108099113%2Cimgsize-1248644.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fbiden-doing-everything-to-improve-visas-process-green-card-backlog-white-house%2Farticleshow%2F108089874.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F108089874.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EUS%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20is%20actively%20working%20to%20improve%20the%20H-1B%20visa%20process%20and%20green%20card%20backlog.%20The%20White%20House%20has%20taken%20actions%20to%20enhance%20the%20H-1B%20visa%20process%20and%20address%20the%20backlog%20for%20lawful%20permanent%20residents%20eligible%20to%20become%20US%20citizens.%20The%20Department%20of%20Homeland%20Security%20has%20published%20a%20final%20rule%20to%20strengthen%20the%20immigration%20system%20and%20reduce%20potential%20fraud.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20World%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22http