ef%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cyient.com%2Fboard-of-directors%2Framesh-abhishek%5C%22%3ERamesh%20Abhishek%3C%2Fa%3E%20(former%20IAS%20officer)%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Fshinjini-kumar-a7b14020%2F%3ForiginalSubdomain%3Din%5C%22%3EShinjini%20Kumar%3C%2Fa%3E%20(former%20RBI%20executive%2C%20former%20CEO%20of%20Paytm%20Payments%20Bank%20and%20an%20entrepreneur)%20were%20the%20independent%20directors%20of%20the%20bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20this%20period%2C%20all%20the%20independent%20directors%20had%20the%20necessary%20expertise%20and%20experience%20of%20being%20part%20of%20corporate%20boards%20and%20the%20role%20of%20independent%20directors.%20When%20a%20bank%20has%20a%20history%20of%20regulatory%20displeasure%20and%20a%20high%20turnover%20of%20chief%20executive%20officers%20(CEOs)%20%E2%80%93%20four%20in%20eight%20years%20%E2%80%93%20independent%20directors%20have%20to%20be%20more%20vigilant%20in%20overseeing%20the%20executive%20and%20demanding%20compliance%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPaytm%20Payments%20Bank%20CEOs%20since%202016%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22141%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECEO%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22161%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDate%20of%20Appointment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22151%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDate%20of%20Resignation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22141%5C%22%3EShinjini%20Kumar%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22161%5C%22%3EMarch%202016%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22151%5C%22%3EJune%202017%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22141%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Frenusatti%2F%3ForiginalSubdomain%3Din%5C%22%3ERenu%20Satti%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22161%5C%22%3EMay%202017%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22151%5C%22%3EJune%202018%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22141%5C%22%3ESatish%20Kumar%20Gupta%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22161%5C%22%3EOctober%202018%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22151%5C%22%3EOctober%202022%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22141%5C%22%3ESurinder%20Chawla%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22161%5C%22%3EFebruary%202023%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22151%5C%22%3E%E2%80%93%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftbody%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftable%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESource%3A%20Paytm%20Payments%20Bank%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fca2013.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2015%2F07%2FSchedule4.pdf%5C%22%3ESchedule%20IV%20Section%20149(8)%20of%20the%20Companies%20Act%2C%202013%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20dealing%20with%20the%20code%20of%20conduct%20for%20independent%20directors%2C%20says%2C%20in%20its%20%E2%80%98role%20and%20functions%E2%80%99%20category%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20independent%20directors%20shall%3A%20(1)%20help%20in%20bringing%20an%20independent%20judgment%20to%20bear%20on%20the%20board%E2%80%99s%20deliberations%2C%20especially%20on%20issues%20of%20strategy%2C%20performance%2C%20risk%20management%2C%20resources%2C%20key%20appointments%20and%20standards%20of%20conduct%3B%20(2)%20bring%20an%20objective%20view%20in%20the%20evaluation%20of%20the%20performance%20of%20the%20board%20and%20management%3B%20(3)%20scrutinise%20the%20performance%20of%20management%20in%20meeting%20agreed%20goals%20and%20objectives%20and%20monitor%20the%20reporting%20of%20performance%3B%20(4)%20satisfy%20themselves%20on%20the%20integrity%20of%20financial%20information%20and%20that%20financial%20controls%20and%20the%20systems%20of%20risk%20management%20are%20robust%20and%20defensible%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20terms%20of%20%E2%80%98duties%E2%80%99%2C%20it%20says%3A%20%E2%80%9CWhere%20they%20%5Bindependent%20directors%5D%20have%20concerns%20about%20the%20running%20of%20the%20company%20or%20a%20proposed%20action%2C%20ensure%20that%20these%20are%20addressed%20by%20the%20Board%20and%2C%20to%20the%20extent%20that%20they%20are%20not%20resolved%2C%20insist%20that%20their%20concerns%20are%20recorded%20in%20the%20minutes%20of%20the%20Board%20meeting%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20RBI%20documents%20various%20violations%20and%20penalises%20a%20bank%2C%20it%20should%20be%20taken%20extremely%20seriously%20by%20the%20board%20of%20directors.%20Typically%2C%20the%20Audit%20Committee%20%E2%80%93%20in%20which%20Vaibhav%20Goel%2C%20Manju%20Agarwal%20and%20Sairee%20Chahal%20were%20present%20as%20independent%20directors%2C%20and%20sometimes%20the%20Risk%20Management%20Committee%2C%20with%20Ramesh%20Abhishek%2C%20Manju%20Agarwal%20and%20Shinjini%20Kumar%20as%20independent%20directors%2C%20will%20examine%20the%20issues%20raised%20by%20RBI%20more%20closely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20board%20appoints%20a%20compliance%20officer%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20issues%20highlighted%20by%20the%20regulator%20are%20addressed.%20A%20time-bound%20compliance%20report%20has%20to%20be%20first%20submitted%20to%20the%20board%2C%20notifying%20that%20the%20bank%20has%20complied%20with%20the%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20directive%20and%20addressed%20its%20concerns.%20This%20report%20is%20thereafter%20sent%20to%20the%20RBI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPaytm%20Payments%20Bank%E2%80%99s%20Audit%20and%20Risk%20Management%20Committee%20in%20FY23%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F28125204%2Fimage-1875.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22892%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F28125204%2Fimage-1875.png%20892w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F28125204%2Fimage-1875-300x105.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-699264%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22311%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20Paytm%20Payments%20Bank%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20the%20Paytm%20Payments%20Bank%E2%80%99s%20board%20of%20directors%2C%20including%20its%20independent%20directors%2C%20during%20this%20period%2C%20abjectly%20failed%20in%20carrying%20out%20their%20role%20and%20duties%20is%20evident%20from%20the%20public%20statements%20made%20by%20senior%20RBI%20officials%20after%20the%20regulator%20asked%20the%20bank%20to%20stop%20incremental%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERBI%20deputy%20governor%20Swaminathan%20J.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstartupstorymedia.com%2Finsights-deputy-governor-states-rbi-sanctions-paytm-payments-bank-for-non-compliance%2F%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20supervisory%20action%20on%20a%20regulated%20entity%20for%20persistent%20non-compliance.%20Such%20actions%20are%20invariably%20preceded%20by%20months%2C%20and%20at%20times%2C%20years%20of%20bilateral%20engagement%20where%20we%20not%20only%20point%20out%20deficiencies%20but%20provide%20more%20than%20adequate%20time%20to%20take%20corrective%20action.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20February%208%2C%202024%2C%20Shaktikanta%20Das%2C%20RBI%20governor%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fbusiness%2Frbi-swaminathan-j-shaktikanta-das-paytm-payments-bank-ppbl-9150621%2F%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CSufficient%20time%20is%20given%20to%20non-compliant%20entities%20but%20action%20is%20taken%20when%20bilateral%20talks%20don%E2%80%99t%20yield%20action.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20shocking%20is%20that%20the%20board%20of%20Paytm%20Payments%20Bank%20had%20two%20experienced%20bankers%2C%20Shinjini%20Kumar%2C%20a%20former%20RBI%20official%20and%20also%20a%20former%20CEO%20of%20Paytm%20Payments%20Bank%2C%20and%20Manju%20Agarwal%2C%20a%20former%20senior%20executive%20of%20SBI.%20Both%20of%20them%20would%20have%20been%20familiar%20with%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20regulatory%20and%20supervisory%20procedures%2C%20as%20well%20as%20KYC%20norms%20for%20banks.%20Yet%2C%20despite%20their%20presence%2C%20the%20bank%20was%20unable%20to%20satisfy%20the%20regulator%E2%80%99s%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20their%20expertise%20and%20experience%2C%20many%20independent%20directors%20are%20selected%20for%20their%20lack%20of%20spine%20in%20protecting%20non-promoter%20interests.%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20founders%2C%20professional%20management%20prefers%20individuals%20who%20do%20not%20grill%20the%20management%2C%20and%20quietly%20acquiesce%20to%20decisions%20which%20may%20be%20adverse%20to%20minority%2Fpublic%20interests.%20The%20conduct%20of%20independent%20directors%20ensures%20not%20only%20the%20extension%20of%20their%20terms%20with%20the%20support%20of%20the%20promoter%2Fmanagement%20but%20also%20qualifies%20them%20eminently%20to%20serve%20on%20the%20boards%20of%20other%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENormally%20independent%20directors%20consist%20of%20chartered%20accountants%20and%20lawyers%20whose%20business%20interests%20are%20intertwined%20with%20the%20corporate%20world%2C%20former%20bureaucrats%2C%20former%20bankers%20and%20retired%20company%20executives%20who%20require%20additional%20income%20or%20prestige%20associated%20with%20the%20corporate%20world.%20As%20technology%20is%20playing%20a%20vital%20role%20in%20business%2C%20boards%20also%20require%20IT%20specialists.%20Till%20date%2C%20independent%20directors%C2%A0%20and%20public%20interest%20directors%20have%20not%20suffered%20the%20consequences%20of%20presiding%20over%20and%20being%20complicit%20in%20poor%20governance%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhemindrahazari.com%2F2020%2F03%2F10%2Fhow-independent-research-found-a-fatal-flaw-with-yes-bank%2F%5C%22%3EYes%20Bank%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhemindrahazari.com%2F2018%2F09%2F18%2Fbehind-ilfs-default-a-board-that-didnt-bark-when-it-was-supposed-to%2F%5C%22%3EIL%26amp%3BFS%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhemindrahazari.com%2F2022%2F02%2F19%2Firresponsibility-or-worse-what-sebis-probe-of-nse-tells-us-about-its-stellar-board-of-directors%2F%5C%22%3ENational%20Stock%20Exchange%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20in%20the%20massive%20siphoning%20of%20funds%20from%20companies%20which%20had%20to%20wind%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20independent%20directors%2C%20who%20are%20seen%20as%20mute%20spectators%2C%20avoid%20annoying%20corporates%20by%20standing%20up%20for%20minority%2Fpublic%20rights%2C%20and%20thereby%20ensure%20that%20they%20will%20be%20invited%20to%20more%20sleeping%20boards.%20They%20are%20rewarded%20for%20being%20silent%20and%20complicit%20in%20misgovernance.%20What%E2%80%99s%20not%20to%20like%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20this%20environment%20is%20changing%20with%20the%20coming%20of%20age%20of%20proxy%20advisory%20firms%2C%20which%20recommend%20to%20their%20institutional%20clients%20how%20to%20vote%20on%20resolutions%2C%20including%20the%20appointment%20and%20re-appointment%20of%20directors.%20Both%20Stakeholders%20Empowerment%20Services%20(SES)%20and%20Institutional%20Investor%20Advisory%20Services%20(IiAS)%20have%20recommended%20not%20to%20support%20Manju%20Agarwal%E2%80%99s%20re-appointment%20as%20an%20independent%20director%20in%20CMS%20Info%20Systems%2C%20on%20account%20of%20her%20poor%20track%20record%20on%20the%20board%20of%20Paytm%20Payments%20Bank.%20The%20SES%20report%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20is%20scathing%20on%20her%20performance%20at%20the%20bank.%20The%20report%20comments%20on%20her%20performance%20in%20the%20light%20of%20the%20prior%20regulatory%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20is%2C%20what%20did%20she%20do%3F%20Did%20she%20use%20her%20experience%20in%20resolving%20the%20issue%3F%20The%20answer%20is%20No.%20The%20problems%20persisted%20and%20culminated%20in%20the%20death%20warrant%20for%20Paytm%20Payments%20Bank.%20Were%20her%20suggestions%20ignored%3F%20Possibly%2C%20but%20if%20she%20can%20resign%20now%20%5B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bseindia.com%2Fxml-data%2Fcorpfiling%2FAttachHis%2F732ff8a8-f500-4d8e-91c7-23041884c994.pdf%5C%22%3Elink%3C%2Fa%3E%5D%2C%20she%20could%20have%20done%20it%20long%20back%2C%20thus%20bringing%20fault%20lines%20of%20the%20bank%20in%20open%20and%20would%20have%20saved%20not%20only%20problems%20faced%20by%20stakeholders%20but%20for%20herself%2C%20as%20SES%20views%20this%20as%20loss%20of%20reputation%20for%20her%20after%20a%20chequered%20career%20at%20the%20premier%20bank.%20Thus%2C%20SES%20concludes%20that%20she%20did%20not%20adhere%20to%20the%20code%20of%20conduct%20as%20envisaged%20and%20failed%20in%20protecting%20the%20institution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20fate%20will%20rightly%20befall%20all%20the%20other%20independent%20directors%20at%20Paytm%20Payments%20Bank%20during%20FY23%20when%20their%20terms%20come%20up%20for%20re-appointment%20or%20if%20they%20are%20mistakenly%20selected%20for%20their%20%E2%80%9Cexpertise%20and%20experience%E2%80%9D%20as%20directors%20in%20other%20companies.%20There%20are%20consequences%20for%20independent%20directors%20who%20sit%20on%20boards%20while%20turning%20a%20blind%20eye%20to%20repeated%20regulatory%20lapses%20and%20sending%20their%20resignations%20immediately%2C%20prior%20or%20post%20stringent%20regulatory%20action%20to%20possibly%20save%20their%20reputation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOther%20directorships%20held%20by%20individuals%20who%20were%20independent%20directors%20of%20Paytm%20Payments%20Bank%20in%20FY22%20and%20FY23%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22209%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Fmanju-agarwal-aa7258a8%2Fdetails%2Fexperience%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EManju%20Agarwal%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22189%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.c