ed-foods-american-diets-2016-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epotential%20health%20risks%20of%20UPFs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20have%20become%20a%20concern%20as%20they%20make%20up%20more%20and%20more%20of%20our%20diets.%20So%20far%2C%20research%20suggests%20that%20UPFs%20are%20not%20as%20healthy%20as%20whole%20foods%20such%20as%20vegetables%2C%20whole%20grains%2C%20and%20beans%2C%20but%20the%20US%20government's%20dietary%20guidelines%20don't%20recommend%20cutting%20them%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20review%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstop-counting-calories-avoid-processed-foods-weight-loss-tim-spector-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edefined%20UPFs%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20industrially%20produced%20foods%20made%20from%20chemically%20modified%20ingredients%20and%20additives%20rather%20than%20whole%20foods%2C%20such%20as%20packaged%20snacks%2C%20carbonated%20soft%20drinks%2C%20instant%20noodles%2C%20and%20readymade%20meals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20the%20studies%20were%20funded%20by%20or%20associated%20with%20ultra-processed%20food%20manufacturers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EUPFs%20were%20linked%20to%20health%20problems%20such%20as%20cardiovascular%20disease%20and%20depression%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20review%20found%20links%20between%20consuming%20UPFs%20and%2032%20health%20issues%2C%20including%20a%20higher%20risk%20of%20dying%20in%20general%2C%20as%20well%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feating-ultra-processed-foods-ovarian-brain-cancer-risk-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecancer%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20mental%2C%20respiratory%2C%20cardiovascular%2C%20gastrointestinal%2C%20and%20metabolic%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20press%20release%2C%20a%2010%25%20increase%20in%20UPF%20consumption%20was%20tied%20to%20a%2012%25%20higher%20risk%20of%20developing%20type%202%20diabetes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeven%20studies%20found%20a%20direct%20link%20between%20eating%20more%20UPFs%20and%20the%20risk%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolorectal-cancer-high-mortality-young-people-signs-symptoms-disease-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecolorectal%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20a%20further%20six%20studies%20found%20that%20the%20risk%20of%20developing%20cardiovascular%20diseases%2C%20which%20include%20heart%20attacks%20and%20coronary%20heart%20disease%2C%20increased%20the%20more%20UPF%20participants%20consumed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20health%20problems%20linked%20to%20eating%20a%20lot%20of%20UPFs%20included%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-lower-blood-pressure-heart-attack-risk-stroke-cardiologist-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHypertension%3C%2Fa%3E%20(high%20blood%20pressure)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EObesity%2C%20especially%20abdominal%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EDeath%20from%20any%20cause%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EAnxiety%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EDepression%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3ESleep%20problems%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20found%20limited%20evidence%20for%20associations%20between%20higher%20UPF%20consumption%20and%20asthma%2C%20non-alcoholic%20fatty%20liver%20disease%2C%20and%20other%20cancers%2C%20including%20breast%2C%20prostate%2C%20and%20pancreatic%20cancers%2C%20chronic%20lymphocytic%20leukemia%2C%20and%20central%20nervous%20system%20tumors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESome%20UPFs%20may%20be%20beneficial%20for%20our%20health%2C%20so%20more%20research%20is%20needed%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEvangeline%20Mantzioris%2C%20program%20director%20of%20nutrition%20and%20food%20sciences%20at%20the%20University%20of%20South%20Australia%2C%20who%20was%20not%20involved%20in%20the%20study%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement%3A%20%26quot%3Bthis%20research%20highlights%20the%20importance%20of%20people%20limiting%20their%20intake%20of%20UPF%20and%20replacing%20it%20with%20whole%20foods.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20researchers%20categorized%20the%20associations%20for%20most%20health%20problems%20as%20%26quot%3Blow%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bvery%20low%26quot%3B%20in%20credibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20the%20team%20acknowledged%20that%20not%20all%20UPFs%20appear%20to%20affect%20health%20in%20the%20same%20way.%20In%20one%20study%2C%20UPFs%20were%20%3Cem%3Egenerally%3C%2Fem%3E%20associated%20with%20a%20higher%20risk%20of%20type%202%20diabetes%2C%20but%20certain%20sub-categories%20of%20UPF%20were%20actually%20associated%20with%20a%20%3Cem%3Elower%3C%2Fem%3E%20risk%20of%20type%202%20diabetes%2C%20such%20as%20ultra-processed%20cereals%2C%20dark%2Fwholegrain%20bread%2C%20packaged%20sweet%20and%20savory%20snacks%2C%20fruit-based%20products%20and%20yogurt%2C%20and%20dairy-based%20desserts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20authors%20of%20the%20study%20recommended%20that%20the%20public%20should%20be%20encouraged%20to%20eat%20fewer%20UPFs%2C%20but%20dietitians%20have%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider%20it's%20unwise%20to%20completely%20cut%20out%20UPFs%2C%20as%20they%20can%20be%20an%20easy%20and%20cheap%20way%20to%20get%20calories%20and%20nutrients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20dietitian%20Taylor%20Grasso%20previously%20told%20BI%20it's%20best%20to%20aim%20for%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprocessed-ultra-processed-foods-ok-to-eat-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E80%3A20%20ratio%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20whole%20to%20processed%20foods%20to%20help%20people%20eat%20healthily%20but%20not%20obsess%20over%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGunter%20Kuhnle%2C%20professor%20of%20nutrition%20and%20food%20science%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Reading%2C%20UK%2C%20who%20was%20also%20not%20involved%20in%20the%20study%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20as%20the%20results%20discussed%20in%20the%20review%20are%20based%20on%20very%20weak%20data%20and%20don't%20touch%20on%20the%20causes%20of%20the%20health%20problems%20mentioned%2C%20they%20don't%20justify%20any%20changes%20in%20dietary%20recommendations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIt's%20unclear%20why%20UPFs%20are%20linked%20to%20so%20many%20health%20problems%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20review%20suggested%20several%20reasons%20why%20UPFs%20might%20be%20linked%20to%20health%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirstly%2C%20a%20person%20who%20eats%20a%20lot%20of%20UPFs%20may%20have%20a%20poor%20diet%20in%20general%2C%20which%20can%20lead%20to%20health%20problems.%20Or%2C%20it%20could%20be%20that%20UPFs%20replace%20nutritious%20foods%20in%20people's%20diets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20additives%20in%20UPFs%2C%20such%20as%20non-sugar%20sweeteners%2C%20emulsifiers%2C%20and%20colorants%2C%20could%20also%20cause%20health%20issues.%20The%20authors%20pointed%20out%20that%20sweeteners%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20have%20been%20classified%20as%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faspartame-is-a-possible-carcinogen-but-still-safe-to-ingest-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epossibly%20carcinogenic%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20International%20Agency%20for%20Research%20on%20Cancer%2C%20although%20at%20levels%20higher%20than%20most%20people%20would%20consume.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20could%20also%20be%20that%20the%20industrial%20processing%20involved%20in%20producing%20UPFs%20or%20the%20packaging%20they%20tend%20to%20come%20in%20could%20contaminate%20the%20foods%20with%20harmful%20substances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20the%20authors%20acknowledged%20that%20they%20don't%20know%20for%20sure%20why%20UPFs%20cause%20these%20issues%2C%20and%20that%20further%20research%20is%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fultra-processed-foods-health-problems-study-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709163061000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65df6b8b6080194819fadad4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F